The paper deals with online reinforcement learning in stochastic games, which involves both machine learning and game theory concepts. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for solving stochastic games, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the interaction between two players, which is a characteristic of multi-agent systems, making cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) a likely category. Finally, the paper deals with Markov environments, which are a type of dynamical system, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category as well.
